        public void setType(String type)
        Parameters:
        type - a String representing the type of source. Should be either 'tcp' or 'jmx'. Not required when 'serviceURL' is set.

      • getType

        Returns:
        a String representing the type of source.

      • getSourceType

        public SourceType getSourceType()
        Returns:
        a SourceType representing the type of source. This is set during validation based on 'serviceURL' if provided, or 'type' if 'serviceURL' is not supplied.

      • getHostname

        public String getHostname()
        Returns:
        a String specifying the hostname where the remote JVM is located.

      • setHostname

        public void setHostname(String hostname)
        Parameters:
        hostname - a String specifying the hostname where the remote JVM is located. Only required if 'serviceURL' is not set.

      • getPort

        public int getPort()
        Returns:
        the port number where JaCoCo data can be accessed on the remote server, either via TCP or JMX. Only required if 'serviceURL' is not set.

      • setPort

        public void setPort(int port)
        Parameters:
        port - the port number where JaCoCo data can be accessed on the remote server, either via TCP or JMX. Only required if 'serviceURL' is not set.

      • setOutputFile

        public void setOutputFile(File outputFile)
        Parameters:
        outputFile - optional File specifying where JaCoCo execution data will be written. If omitted, defaults to '${project.build.directory}/jacocotogo/jacoco[n].exec' where [n] is a index which corresponds to the order of the source.

      • getOutputFile

        public File getOutputFile()
        Returns:
        File specifying where JaCoCo execution data will be written.

      • getUsername

        Returns:
        the String representing the username for authentication to JMX server.

      • setUsername

        public void setUsername(String username)
        Parameters:
        username - the String representing the username for authentication to JMX server. Only necessary if authentication is enabled on the JMX location.

      • getPassword

        public String getPassword()
        Returns:
        the String representing the password for authentication to JMX server.

      • setPassword

        public void setPassword(String password)
        Parameters:
        password - the String representing the password for authentication to JMX server. Only necessary if authentication is enabled on the JMX location.

      • getServiceURL

        public String getServiceURL()
        Returns:
        a String with the serviceURL representing where the jacoco data can be retrieved. If the serviceURL is specified it takes precedence over the type, hostname, and port parameters.

      • setServiceURL

        public void setServiceURL(String serviceURL)
        Parameters:
        serviceURL - a String of the serviceURL representing where the jacoco data can be retrieved. For JMX access see JMXServiceURL for format details. For TCP access the serviceURL should take the format: 'tcp://myhost.mydomain.com:port' If the serviceURL is specified it takes precedence over the 'type', 'hostname', and 'port' parameters.

      • isResetAfterFetch
